cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.GR, cs.IR 

The paper uses computer vision techniques based on deep convolutional neural networks to analyze patterns in land use in urban neighborhoods using large-scale satellite imagery data. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also uses machine learning techniques to train and compare deep architectures, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper deals with geospatial data, which could place it in cs.GR (Graphics) or cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
